---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement | James Tannahill"
  description="Accessibility commitment and contact information for jamestannahill.com."
  canonical="https://www.jamestannahill.com/accessibility"
>
  <div class="bg-white min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

      <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-[28px] font-semibold tracking-tight mb-2" style="color:#1a1a1a;">Accessibility Statement</h1>
      <p class="text-[12px] mb-12" style="color:#999;">Last reviewed: April 2026</p>

      <!-- Commitment -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Our Commitment</p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4" style="color:#444;">
          jamestannahill.com is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We
          strive to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA, published by the
          World Wide Web Consortium (W3C).
        </p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85]" style="color:#444;">
          Accessibility is an ongoing priority, not a one-time task. We continuously review and improve the
          Site as standards evolve and as we learn from user feedback.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Technical Measures -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Technical Measures</p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4" style="color:#444;">
          The following measures have been implemented to support accessibility:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] pl-5 list-disc" style="color:#444;">
          <li>
            <strong>Semantic HTML</strong> - Page structure uses appropriate heading hierarchy, landmark elements
            (<code class="text-[13px] px-1 rounded" style="background:#f5f5f5; color:#555;">main</code>,
            <code class="text-[13px] px-1 rounded" style="background:#f5f5f5; color:#555;">nav</code>,
            <code class="text-[13px] px-1 rounded" style="background:#f5f5f5; color:#555;">footer</code>),
            and descriptive labels to assist screen readers and assistive technologies
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Keyboard navigation</strong> - All interactive elements (links, form fields, buttons) are
            reachable and operable via keyboard alone
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Color contrast</strong> - Text and UI elements maintain contrast ratios meeting WCAG AA
            standards (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Focus indicators</strong> - Keyboard focus is visually indicated for all interactive elements
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Responsive design</strong> - The Site is fully responsive and accessible across desktop,
            tablet, and mobile viewport sizes
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Form labels</strong> - Contact form fields include visible labels and accessible name
            attributes to support assistive technology
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Video Content -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Video Content</p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85]" style="color:#444;">
          Background video content on the Site is decorative in nature. All videos are muted by default and
          do not autoplay audio content. Videos do not convey information essential to understanding the page,
          and their absence does not affect the ability of any user to access the substantive content of the Site.
          Video playback does not interfere with screen reader operation or assistive technology.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Known Limitations -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Known Limitations</p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85]" style="color:#444;">
          While we strive for full WCAG 2.1 AA conformance, some areas of the Site may not yet fully meet all
          criteria. We are aware that accessibility audits are ongoing, and we are committed to addressing any
          identified gaps. If you encounter a specific barrier, please report it so we can address it promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Feedback -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Feedback & Contact</p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4" style="color:#444;">
          We welcome feedback on the accessibility of this Site. If you experience any barriers that prevent
          you from accessing content or using any feature, please contact us:
        </p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4" style="color:#444;">
          <a href="mailto:web@jamestannahill.com" class="underline hover:opacity-70" style="color:var(--color-amber);">web@jamestannahill.com</a>
        </p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85]" style="color:#444;">
          Please describe the accessibility issue you encountered, the assistive technology you are using (if any),
          and the page or feature where the problem occurred. We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within
          5 business days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Standards Reference -->
      <section class="mb-4">
        <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Standards Reference</p>
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85]" style="color:#444;">
          This statement references the
          <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline hover:opacity-70" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1</a>,
          published by the W3C Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI). WCAG defines requirements for making web
          content more accessible to people with disabilities.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
